nce we have `Matrix4::Translation()` to return the translation, wouldn't it make more sense to have a function `SetTranslation` to set it and have `Translate` add the translation?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>The documentation is <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/src/6d684eb7c3b669c6db6a18f468d40802e3c60e00/include/ignition/math/Matrix4.hh?at=default#Matrix4.hh-176\" rel=\"nofollow\">clear</a>, the function <strong>sets the translation</strong>. But the function name suggests it would <strong>add the translation</strong>.</p>\n<p>Since we have <code>Matrix4::Translation()</code> to return the translation, wouldn't it make more sense to have a function <code>SetTranslation</code> to set it and have <code>Translate</code> add the translation?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "resolved", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2015-09-01T21:42:13.750166+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2017-12-19T17:54:18.602471+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 30}